  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why do IIT's and NIT's in India get so much domestic admiration when most of them do not feature anywhere in top 100 globally?",
  "response": "The Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) and the National Institutes of Technology (NITs) command significant domestic admiration for several reasons, even though many do not appear in the top 100 universities globally. Here are some key factors contributing to their prestige in India:\n\n1. **Quality of Education**: IITs and NITs are known for their rigorous academic programs, strong emphasis on engineering and technology, and high standards of education. They produce graduates with solid technical skills and problem-solving abilities.\n\n2. **Entrance Exams**: Admission to IITs and NITs is highly competitive, based primarily on the Joint Entrance Examination (JEE). The difficulty of the entrance exams creates an impression of exclusivity and excellence, further enhancing the institutions' prestige.\n\n3. **Successful Alumni**: Many IIT and NIT graduates have gone on to achieve remarkable success in various fields, including technology, entrepreneurship, academia, and research. High-profile alumni also contribute to the institutions' reputation.\n\n4. **Industry Connections**: IITs often have strong ties with industry, leading to excellent internship and job placement opportunities for their graduates. Many globally recognized companies actively recruit from these institutions.\n\n5. **Research Contributions**: Though they may not rank in the top 100 globally, IITs and NITs contribute significantly to research and innovation in India. Their contributions to technology, engineering, and sciences are noteworthy and have a strong regional impact.\n\n6. **Government Support**: These institutions receive substantial support from the Indian government in terms of funding, infrastructure, and policy backing, making them some of the best-resourced engineering schools in the country.\n\n7. **Cultural Significance**: IITs hold a special place in Indian society, representing aspirations for many families and being viewed as gateways to upward mobility and socio-economic progress.\n\n8. **Perception of Quality**: The branding and historical significance of IITs as premier institutions of engineering and technology in India leads to a strong perception of quality among the domestic population, irrespective of global rankings.\n\n9. **Global Collaborations**: While they may not feature in the top global rankings, many IITs engage in international collaborations and partnerships, further enhancing their academic credibility and recognition.\n\nIn summary, the domestic admiration for IITs and NITs stems from their challenging admissions process, academic rigor, successful alumni, industry connections, and a cultural perception of excellence, making them highly respected institutions in India despite their relative global rankings.",
